findings.chest: The visualized lung bases are clear. There is no pericardial or pleural effusion.
abdomen: The portal venous system is patent.
No evidence of intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation.
Gallbladder is normal and without gallstones.
The inferior vena cava has a plump appearance.
The spleen and adrenal glands are unremarkable.
The pancreas enhances homogenously and is without focal lesions.
The kidneys display symmetric nephrograms and excretion of contrast. No focal renal lesions. No hydronephrosis. Ureters are normal in caliber and course to the bladder.
The stomach is decompressed. The small bowel is normal in caliber without focal wall thickening. The large bowel is normal in caliber.
High-density material within portions of small and large bowel, may be related to ingested material.
The appendix is dilated measuring up to 14 mm and is air and fluid filled with extensive surrounding fat stranding.
An appendicolith is noted in the body of the appendix.
Mild thickening of the proximal ascending colon/cecum.
No extraluminal air or drainable fluid collection.
The abdominal aorta and its major branches are patent, normal in course and caliber.
No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy by CT size criteria.
pelvis: The bladder is well distended and normal.
No pelvic side-wall or inguinal lymphadenopathy by CT size criteria.
Trace pelvic free fluid, likely reactive.
findings.osseous_structures: No focal lytic or sclerotic lesion concerning for malignancy.
